# AR-local configuration

Python ingest and export scripts plus a **local HTTP dashboard** (`cdr_dashboard_server.py`, `dashboard/`). No Cloudflare Workers or Pages in this repo.

## Hosting model

- **Dashboard:** `python cdr_dashboard_server.py --exports <runs/<date>/_exports>` (see README).
- **Shell assets:** `/site/*` is served from the AustralianRates **`site`** directory (auto-detected beside this repo or via **`--site-root`**). Prefer a tree that contains **`assets/banks/*.png`** when multiple candidates exist.
- **Bundled:** **`/assets/ar-bank-brand.js`** is served from **`dashboard/ar-bank-brand.js`** so brand icons resolve without a working **`/site/ar-bank-brand.js`**.

## Repo commands

| Purpose | Command |
|--------|---------|
| Local dashboard smoke | `npm run verify:local -- --base-url=<url>/` |
| Bot wait | `npm run wait-for-bots` |
| Open PR closeout guard | `npm run ship:closeout:strict` |

## Verification checklist

- HTTP smoke passes (**`verify:local`**).
- No unexpected console errors on the dashboard when exercising changed UI (Browser MCP when requested).
- Critical flows: index loads, **`/api/latest`** returns JSON for the configured exports path.

## Fix-restart-retry

If checks fail: fix, restart the dashboard server if Python or static files changed, re-run **`verify:local`**.

## Code quality (aligned with Australian Rates)

- Soft target **~800 LOC** per file, hard ceiling **~1000 LOC**; split along natural seams when practical.
- Cap functions around **~50 lines** where reasonable; avoid duplicating the same logic in 3+ places.
